# I2C address scan: count responding slaves.
*scan(present as Vec of i64, n as i64) returns i64
    c is 0
    i is 0
    while i < n
        if present.get(i) equals 1
            c is c + 1
        i is i + 1
    c

*main
    p is vec()
    i is 0
    while i < 128
        if i % 17 equals 0
            p.push(1)
        else
            p.push(0)
        i is i + 1
    log scan(p, 128)
